('Physics', 'Kinematics & Motion in a Straight Line', 'MCQ', 'Hard', '[Physics Hard Q1] A body is projected vertically upwards with velocity 10 m/s. Calculate maximum height H.', '{"A": "5.0 m", "B": "10.0 m", "C": "2.5 m", "D": "3.3 m"}'::jsonb, 'A', 'Step-by-step NCERT solution breakdown for Q1: Using third equation of motion v^2 = u^2 - 2gH => H = u^2/2g.', 'Step-by-step NCERT solution breakdown for Q1: Using third equation of motion v^2 = u^2 - 2gH => H = u^2/2g.', 'Kinematics & Motion in a Straight Line', '{"positive": 4, "negative": 1}'::jsonb),
('Physics', 'Laws of Motion & Friction', 'MCQ', 'Medium', '[Physics Hard Q2] A block of mass 3 kg rests on a rough horizontal surface with coefficient of friction mu = 0.2. Minimum force required to move it is:', '{"A": "6.0 N", "B": "12.0 N", "C": "3.0 N", "D": "18.0 N"}'::jsonb, 'A', 'Step-by-step NCERT solution breakdown for Q2: F_min = mu * m * g = {mu} * {m} * 10 = {f_min} N.', 'Step-by-step NCERT solution breakdown for Q2: F_min = mu * m * g = {mu} * {m} * 10 = {f_min} N.', 'Laws of Motion & Friction', '{"positive": 4, "negative": 1}'::jsonb),
