('Physics', 'Ray Optics (Pictorial / Ray Diagram)', 'MCQ', 'Medium', '[Physics Hard Q4] [Diagrammatic Q] In the ray diagram below, a light ray passes through a glass prism of refracting angle 60 deg at minimum deviation delta_m = 30 deg. The refractive index mu of prism material is:', '{"A": "sqrt(2)", "B": "1.5", "C": "sqrt(3)", "D": "1.33"}'::jsonb, 'A', 'Step-by-step NCERT solution breakdown for Q4: mu = sin((A+delta_m)/2)/sin(A/2) = sin 45 / sin 30 = sqrt(2).', 'Step-by-step NCERT solution breakdown for Q4: mu = sin((A+delta_m)/2)/sin(A/2) = sin 45 / sin 30 = sqrt(2).', 'Ray Optics (Pictorial / Ray Diagram)', '{"positive": 4, "negative": 1}'::jsonb),
